# Express API conventions

Follow `docs/03-architecture/api-contract.md`.

## Router pattern

- One router per resource in `src/routes/`
- Mount in `src/index.js` with plural path: `/students`, `/stripes`, `/attendance`
- Use `requireAuth` from `src/middleware/auth.js` on all coach routes

## Supabase access

- Import `supabase` from `src/lib/supabase.js` (service role client)
- Table names: `students`, `stripes`, `attendance`, `waivers` — lowercase only
- Match column names in DB: `belt_level`, `join_date`, `student_id`, `stripe_number`, `session_date`, `waiver_active`

## Request / response

- JSON body via `express.json()`
- Validation: return `400` with `{ error: '...' }` for missing required fields
- Supabase errors: return `500` with `{ error: error.message }`
- Not found: return `404` with `{ error: '...' }`
- Delete success: return `204` with empty body

## Auth

- Read `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` header
- Validate via `supabase.auth.getUser(token)` — attach `req.user` on success
- Do not add separate JWT verification; Supabase Auth is the source of truth

## Phase 2 additions (not yet implemented)

- CORS middleware before routes
- Centralized error handler
- Zod validation on request bodies
